  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who has shown remorse by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While the breach of trust is significant, a multi-year sentence is disproportionate for the amount of $25,000. Considering the nature of the crime, the lack of a prior record, and the focus on restitution, a period of 6 months in a correctional facility is sufficient to serve as a deterrent and a just punishment, disregarding the disruptive and emotional outbursts of spectators.",
  "verdict": 6
}
